title: Policy6005(s1)
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

The Regional School District No. 8 Board of Education (the "Board") considers that the most appropriate educational setting for students is within a formal school structure. The Board believes that the formal school structure provides students with the opportunity to interact with other students and with professionally trained adults that is difficult to emulate in the home setting.
